md:
giải nghĩa từ "abnormal" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan.

* Abnormal (adjective)
	+ Meaning: Not normal or usual; not typical or expected.
	+ Vietnamese: Không bình thường; bất thường.
	+ Example sentence: The abnormal test results indicated that the patient had a serious illness.
	+ Related words: normal, usual, typical, expected.

* Abnormal (noun)
	+ Meaning: Something that is not normal or usual.
	+ Vietnamese: Sự bất thường; điều không bình thường.
	+ Example sentence: The abnormal growth on the skin was a sign of cancer.
	+ Related words: normality, usualness, typicality.

Note: The word "abnormal" can have different meanings depending on the context in which it is used. In general, it refers to something that is not normal or usual, but it can also imply a deviation from a standard or a norm.
